<item>
            <title>[LU-9879] conf-sanity test 80 fails with &#8220;Failed to start MDT&#8221;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9879</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When run with a separate MGS and MDS or MGT and MDT, conf-sanity test_80 fails with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;conf-sanity test_80: @@@@@@ FAIL: Failed to start MDT 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When test 80 is run alone and all servers are already mounted, then the test will pass. If test 80 is run in sequence with all the other conf-sanity tests and there is a separate MGS and MDS, then the test fails because, the first thing is does is try to mount the MDS. The test does not consider if there is a separate MGS or not. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One fix for this issue is to change call start_mgsmds() instead of start_mds().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other conf-sanity test may suffer from this same issue; test 84 and 100 are examples.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Related to this, there are some tests that start an MDT, with start_mdt(), but need to start the MGS, start_mgs(),first. conf-sanity test 87, 104, 105 and 107 are examples of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logs for this test failure are at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/39fe026c-8068-11e7-8825-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/39fe026c-8068-11e7-8825-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
